Hanlie Gouws, News24Police officers on the scene of the shootout in Sandton. (Lizeka Tandwa, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Four people, three of them believed to be hijackers, were injured in a shootout in Sandton after an alleged Robbery in Rivonia on Wednesday.The shootout occurred in Grayston Drive and Katherine Street in Sandton, reportedly after the police chased a gang after a hijacking incident.Three of the suspects were arrested and one got away and is still at large.Police spokesperson Kay Makhubele told the Sandton Chronicle that officers were following up on a lead when the suspects were spotted in a white Mercedes. They chased the men and a shootout ensued."Three are in custody and one ran away," he said.&nbsp;A firearm and a hijacked vehicle was recovered.According to ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring, one of the injured&nbsp;was a security guard who sustained minor injuries when he climbed a barbed-wire fence and the other three were the three suspects.He told News24 that the suspects were apparently injured during the chase and did not sustain bullet wounds in the shootout.&nbsp;No serious injuries were reported.READ: Shootout in SandtonEmergency medical service EMER-G-MED said in a statement that on-scene reports indicated that the suspects' vehicle was spotted by police travelling on the highway. "The suspects opened fire and a shootout ensued."&nbsp;Traffic came to a standstill and delays would continue while the scene&nbsp;was processed. [UPDATE] - Pictures from the shootout on the M1 near Grayston Road. Please avoid this area. @ewnupdates @eNCA @JacaNews @_ArriveAlive pic.twitter.com/ktv0QybR8R24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.